description: Feeling excessively cold could be more than just winter's chill. Your body might be signaling nutrient deficiencies. Feeling colder than others isn’t always a matter of personal tolerance—it could be a sign that your body lacks the nutrients it needs to stay warm. Ensuring your diet includes these nutrients can make a noticeable difference in how your body responds to cold temperatures.
title: Do you feel extra cold? It can be because of this vitamin deficiency

description: Kolkata Knight Riders bought back Venkatesh Iyer for a whopping Rs 23.75 crore.  They outbid Royal Challengers Bangalore in a fierce bidding war.  KKR sees Iyer as a potential captain.  He was a key player in their 2024 title win.  Iyer's batting prowess and leadership qualities make him a valuable asset. KKR believes he is worth the investment.
title: Explained: Why KKR bid Rs 23.75 crore for Venkatesh Iyer

description: Pakistani TikTok star Kanwal Aftab is the latest victim of a personal video leak, the fourth such incident involving prominent influencers in recent weeks. Aftab, known for her engaging content and modeling career, has yet to address the circulating videos.
title: After Minahil Malik & Imsha Rehman; model Kanwal Aftab obscene videos leaked online

description: A viral video claims Ganga water's purity. Ashu Ghai's video shows microscopic examination and lab tests of Gangajal from Haridwar revealing no impurities or microorganisms, even after culturing. This contradicts reports deeming Ganga water unfit for drinking, while aligning with an IIT-Kanpur study finding certain stretches potable.
title: Ganga jal was put under microscope & this is what came to light

description: Top diplomats Blinken and Jaishankar met in Italy. They discussed global security and the growing US-India partnership.  Both nations want to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific.  They also talked about technology, clean energy, and investment opportunities.  Jaishankar mentioned the Quad's evolution and Indo-Pacific dynamics.  He looks forward to welcoming Blinken to India in 2025.
title: India, US stronger when working together: Antony Blinken

description: Israeli fighter jets struck 20 Hezbollah targets in Beirut. The targets included financial and military infrastructure.  Israel issued evacuation warnings before the two-minute operation.  The strikes occurred just before a ceasefire agreement.
title: Watch: Israeli Air Force hits 20 Hezbollah targets in 120 seconds

description: An IIT Bombay student lost over Rs 7 lakh in a digital arrest scam.  Fraudsters posed as TRAI and police officials. They made false money laundering accusations. The student was tricked into transferring money via UPI and sharing bank details.
title: IIT-Bombay student loses Rs 7 lakh to 'digital arrest scam': WhatsApp call & more

description: Rishabh Pant secured a record-breaking Rs 27 crore deal with the Lucknow Super Giants (LSG) at the IPL 2025 mega auction, making him the highest-paid player in IPL history. Delhi Capitals tried to retain him, but LSG's aggressive bid prevailed. After recovering from a serious car accident, Pant will captain LSG in the upcoming season starting March 14.
title: How much will Pant earn after tax from Rs 27 cr salary?

description: Andhra Pradesh deputy chief minister Pawan Kalyan condemned the arrest of Iskcon priest Chinmoy Krishna Das in Bangladesh, urging collective action and intervention from Bangladesh's interim leader Muhammad Yunus and the UN. Kalyan highlighted India's historical support for Bangladesh and expressed concern over the targeting of Hindus.
title: 'Stop atrocities on Hindus': Pawan Kalyan slams Iskcon priest's arrest in B'desh

description: Several prominent cricketers, including David Warner and Kane Williamson, went unsold at the recent IPL auction in Jeddah.  An 'Unsold XI' featuring these players boasts remarkable talent and can rival any of the 10 teams. Timesofindia.com put together a playing XI from that list, with Williamson as the team's skipper.
title: The 'Unsold XI' of IPL Auction 2025

description: Five doctors from Uttar Pradesh University of Medical Sciences, Saifai, were killed in a road accident on the Agra-Lucknow Expressway.  Their vehicle collided with a truck early Wednesday morning while returning from a wedding in Lucknow. One passenger survived and is receiving treatment.  Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath expressed condolences and directed an on-site assessment.
title: 5 doctors die in road accident on Agra-Lucknow Expressway

description: Thirteen-year-old cricketer Vaibhav Suryavanshi, from a small village in Bihar, has landed a record-breaking Rs 1.10 crore deal with Rajasthan Royals in the IPL auction. His father, Sanjeev, a farmer and part-time journalist, learned of the news from his son, currently playing for India's U19 team in Dubai.
title: IPL Auction: How Vaibhav impressed RR by hitting 3 consecutive sixes

description: Indian-American scientist Jay Bhattacharya, a staunch critic of pandemic lockdowns and vaccine mandates, has been tapped by former US President Donald Trump to lead the National Institutes of Health (NIH). Bhattacharya, a Stanford professor, will partner with Robert F. Kennedy Jr., Trump's HHS nominee. This marks Trump's first Indian-American nomination for a senior role.
title: Who is Jay Bhattacharya? Indian-American named Trump’s pick for top US health institute

description: The IPL 2025 mega auction witnessed record-breaking bids. Rishabh Pant became the most expensive player ever, acquired by Lucknow Super Giants for Rs 27 crore. Shreyas Iyer followed closely at Rs 26.75 crore, joining Punjab Kings. Venkatesh Iyer returned to Kolkata Knight Riders for Rs 23.75 crore, expressing his readiness to lead the team.
title: These players will earn more than Virat Kohli in IPL 2025

description: Royal Challengers Bangalore finalized their 22-member squad for the upcoming IPL season.  Retaining Virat Kohli, Rajat Patidar and Yash Dayal before the auction, RCB invested heavily in Liam Livingstone, Phil Salt, Jitesh Sharma and Josh Hazlewood.  The revamped squad aims to secure their first Indian Premier League title.
title: IPL, RCB squad: Final team, full list, price tags after mega auction

description: Indian fast bowler Umran Malik expresses excitement about joining Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) for IPL 2025 after being acquired for Rs 75 lakh. Recovered from injuries and focused on improving his game, Malik aims to secure a spot in the Indian team through strong IPL performance. During his time at SRH, Umran learned from pace legend Dale Steyn and shared the dressing room with seasoned campaigners like Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Marco Jansen, and Pat Cummins.
title: Umran Malik after KKR deal: 'I am going to kill it'

description: A 17-year-old tribal girl in Chhattisgarh was repeatedly gang-raped by four government officials, including her school's principal, headmaster, and a teacher, along with a forest ranger. The assaults were filmed and used to blackmail the victim.  Police have arrested all four accused and are investigating the possibility of others involved.
title: Tribal minor gangraped twice by school principal, headmaster, teacher & forest ranger
Maharashtra set to lose out on mega refinery, talks on with Gujarat & Andhra

description: Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional pace bowling stats have sparked debate about his place among India's all-time greats, particularly in comparison to Kapil Dev. While Bumrah's current numbers are impressive, experts like Sunil Gavaskar and former players emphasize Kapil's achievements in a less supportive era.
title: Is Jasprit Bumrah the greatest ever Indian fast bowler?

description: Violence erupted in Jiribam, Manipur.  The Centre and state governments launched combing operations to catch the culprits.  The National Investigation Agency will investigate the killings.  The government considers lifting the Armed Forces Special Powers Act in some areas.  A missing person case is under investigation.  The chief minister urges calm and cooperation.
title: Manipur violence: Mass combing op launched in Jiribam; CM appeals for calm

description: The Adani Group has denied bribery allegations leveled by the US Department of Justice and the US Securities and Exchange Commission. Adani Green Energy Ltd clarified that its executives, including Gautam Adani, Sagar Adani, and Vneet Jaain, were not charged with FCPA violations but face charges related to securities and wire fraud.
title: Adani Group denies bribery allegations by US against Gautam, Sagar and Vneet Jaain

description: Apple's AI rollout in China faces regulatory challenges. The company may need to partner with a Chinese firm. This collaboration will ensure compliance with local laws. Apple has spoken with several Chinese tech companies. Sales in China have recently dipped. The launch of Apple Intelligence is crucial for Apple's market share there.
title: Apple’s plan to launch AI for iPhones in China will be 'difficult and long process'
Pakistan security forces launch midnight raid on Imran Khan's supporters

description: Wrestler Bajrang Punia received a four-year suspension from NADA for refusing a doping test during team trials.  Punia contested the charge, citing concerns over expired testing kits used previously by NADA, but the agency upheld the ban.  The suspension prevents Punia from competing and coaching internationally. He claims his protest against former WFI President influenced the NADA's decision.
title: Wrestler Bajrang Punia suspended for 4 years by NADA

description: Iskcon Bangladesh condemns the arrest of Sanatani leader Chinmoy Krishna Das, voicing concern over escalating attacks on the community. They demand accountability for the attacks, protection of minority rights, and measures to ensure peace. Other groups like BHBCUC echo these concerns, warning of potential damage to Bangladesh's international image.
title: 'Discrimination must not be tolerated': Iskcon slams Chinmoy Krishna Das' arrest

description: Israel and Hezbollah agreed to a ceasefire in Lebanon.  Israeli troops and Hezbollah will withdraw.  UN peacekeepers will deploy.  The US will lead an international monitoring group.  The Gaza conflict is not part of this agreement.  Hezbollah's support depends on Israel halting attacks.
title: Israel & Hezbollah reach ceasefire deal for Lebanon: What are terms of agreement?

description: Prime Minister Modi, addressing the Supreme Court's 75th Constitution Day celebration, emphasized his commitment to staying within the executive's constitutional boundaries. He indirectly responded to criticism, particularly from SCBA president Kapil Sibal, regarding judicial independence. Modi also paid tribute to 26/11 victims and vowed a strong response to terrorism.
title: Never encroached on other pillars of governance: PM Modi

description: Mohammed Shami, India's veteran fast bowler, will join Sunrisers Hyderabad for Rs 10 crore in the upcoming IPL season. Gujarat Titans, Shami's former team, opted not to use their Right-to-Match card despite initially considering retaining him. GT's coach, Ashish Nehra, explained that their retention strategy faced limitations due to the auction dynamics and Shami's high price.
title: 'Mohammed Shami was part of GT's retention plans but...'

description: Following her presidential election defeat to Donald Trump, Vice President Kamala Harris released a brief, subdued video message. Returning from a post-election holiday, Harris urged supporters to retain their power and purpose, echoing sentiments from before the November 5th election. While her motivation remains unclear, the message comes as Trump's transition progresses, with his inauguration set for January 20, 2025.
title: 'Don't let anybody take your power': Kamala Harris' message to supporters

description: Pakistan's hosting of the Champions Trophy is in jeopardy due to political instability, with a hybrid model or relocation looking increasingly likely. Former cricketer Basit Ali suggests the ICC's November 29 meeting may be irrelevant as Sri Lanka's A team's withdrawal highlights security concerns.
title: Hybrid Champions Trophy after political unrest in Pakistan?

description: The Supreme Court dismissed a plea to revert to paper ballots, stating that only losing candidates suspect EVM tampering.  The petitioner argued that even Elon Musk acknowledged EVM vulnerabilities, citing concerns raised by both Chandrababu Naidu and Jagan Mohan Reddy after electoral losses. The court highlighted previous dismissals of similar petitions, emphasizing EVM security.
title: Supreme Court junks ballot plea: ‘EVM tampered when you lose'

description: GitHub now predicts India will become the world's largest developer hub in 2028, a year later than initially projected. CEO Thomas Dohmke cites global economic factors and the US's AI-driven growth as reasons for the delay. While India's developer count hit 17 million in 2023, Dohmke remains optimistic about India's long-term potential, citing its robust startup scene and government backing.
title: GitHub CEO: At Microsoft and GitHub, we’re not worried about AI …
Udaipur clashes: Day after royal rumble, authorities step in

description: Tensions escalated in Chittagong, Bangladesh, following a court's refusal to grant bail to Hindu priest Chinmoy Krishna Das, accused of sedition. The court's order against the priest charged with sedition triggered violent clashes between supporters of the monk and law enforcement forces who were joined by locals, leaving at least one dead and many others injured. Eyewitnesses identified the victim as Saiful Islam Alif (35), a lawyer, alleging that he was hacked to death by protesters.
title: India-Bangladesh tensions mount as Hindu priest jailed for 'sedition'
Adani stock rout worsens on Moody's, Fitch's '-ve outlook'

description: Russia seeks to invest in and expand train and component manufacturing within India to fulfill its domestic needs.  Russian railway company TMH expressed interest, aiming to establish production facilities in India and potentially supply back to Russia.  TMH, involved in the Vande Bharat sleeper coach project, plans to source components from India and other nations, unaffected by current sanctions.
title: Russia eyes India for train manufacturing to meet some domestic demand
Maharashtra polls: 60 got over 1 lakh votes but still on losing side

description: A Singapore Airlines Airbus A380 experienced a rollback incident after docking at Delhi's IGI Airport Monday night. Pilots reportedly forgot to engage the parking brake, causing the double-decker aircraft to roll slightly on the sloped parking bay. No collision occurred, and the pilots quickly rectified the error.
title: Pilots ‘forget’ to apply brake, plane rolls back at Delhi airport's parking bay

description: A 30-year-old Haryana man, Rahul Jat, accused of being a serial killer, has been arrested in Gujarat for the rape and murder of a 19-year-old girl. After the crime, he calmly ate fruit salad and traveled to Vadodara. Police investigations reveal his potential involvement in at least four other murders across multiple states.
title: Serial killer relished fruit salad after raping, killing 19-year-old girl in Gujarat

description: Elon Musk defended his Mars colonization plans against Neil deGrasse Tyson's criticism, emphasizing its importance for humanity's long-term survival.  Tyson questioned the financial viability of the project, while Musk clarified it wasn't an investment but a crucial step to safeguard consciousness.
title: Elon Musk clears 'doubts' on Mars colonisation plans: 'I’m not going...'

description: Indian Railways allows passengers to modify confirmed train tickets. Name changes are possible offline for family members, requiring a written request and ID proof at least 24 hours before departure. Date changes are permitted for both offline and online tickets, but online modifications involve cancellation and rebooking. Offline date changes require a 48-hour notice.
title: How to change name and date in booked train ticket online and offline
